description: Kokugiwon, also known as the World Taekwondo Headquarters, was inaugurated on November 30, 1972. Its functions include being responsible for taekwondo dan rank examinations and issuing dan rank certificates, and engaging in taekwondo research work. Kokugiwon is the only legal dan awarding organization recognized by the World Taekwondo Federation (WTF). WTF itself does not issue dan or black belt certificates. In fact, the WTF and Kokugiwon are two separate organizations, but they are often confused, for example, "WTF" is often referred to as Kokugiwon-style taekwondo.

description: M! CountdownMwave is a music chart program of the Korean Mnet channel. It selects the top 50 pop music charts every week and invites singers and bands to perform live music works.
